  54:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h **** // Due to the use of unmasked pointers, this FIFO does not suffer from losing
  55:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h **** // one item slice. Furthermore, write and read operations are completely
  56:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h **** // decoupled as write and read functions do not modify a common state. Henceforth,
  57:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h **** // writing or reading from the FIFO within an ISR is safe as long as no other
  58:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h **** // process (thread or ISR) interferes.
  59:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h **** // Also, this FIFO is ready to be used in combination with a DMA as the write and
  60:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h **** // read pointers can be updated from within a DMA ISR. Overflows are detectable
  61:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h **** // within a certain number (see tu_fifo_overflow()).
  62:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h **** 
  63:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h **** /* Write/Read "pointer" is in the range of: 0 .. depth - 1, and is used to get the fifo data.
  64:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  * Write/Read "index" is always in the range of: 0 .. 2*depth-1
  65:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *
  66:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  * The extra window allow us to determine the fifo state of empty or full with only 2 indices
  67:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  * Following are examples with depth = 3
  68:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *
  69:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  * - empty: W = R
  70:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *                |
  71:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *    -------------------------
  72:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *    | 0 | RW| 2 | 3 | 4 | 5 |
  73:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *
  74:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  * - full 1: W > R
  75:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *                |
  76:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *    -------------------------
  77:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *    | 0 | R | 2 | 3 | W | 5 |
  78:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *
  79:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  * - full 2: W < R
  80:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *                |
  81:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *    -------------------------
  82:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *    | 0 | 1 | W | 3 | 4 | R |
  83:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *
  84:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  * - Number of items in the fifo can be determined in either cases:
  85:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *    - case W >= R: Count = W - R
  86:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *    - case W <  R: Count = 2*depth - (R - W)
ARM GAS  /tmp/cci2pXLM.s 			page 71


  87:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *
  88:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  * In non-overwritable mode, computed Count (in above 2 cases) is at most equal to depth.
  89:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  * However, in over-writable mode, write index can be repeatedly increased and count can be
  90:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  * temporarily larger than depth (overflowed condition) e.g
  91:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *
  92:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *  - Overflowed 1: write(3), write(1)
  93:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *    In this case we will adjust Read index when read()/peek() is called so that count = depth.
  94:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *                  |
  95:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *      -------------------------
  96:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *      | R | 1 | 2 | 3 | W | 5 |
  97:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *
  98:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *  - Double Overflowed i.e index is out of allowed range [0,2*depth)
  99:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *    This occurs when we continue to write after 1st overflowed to 2nd overflowed. e.g:
 100:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *      write(3), write(1), write(2)
 101:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *    This must be prevented since it will cause unrecoverable state, in above example
 102:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *    if not handled the fifo will be empty instead of continue-to-be full. Since we must not modif
 103:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *    read index in write() function, which cause race condition. We will re-position write index s
 104:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *    after data is written it is a full fifo i.e W = depth - R
 105:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *
 106:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *      re-position W = 1 before write(2)
 107:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *      Note: we should also move data from mem[3] to read index as well, but deliberately skipped 
 108:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *      since it is an expensive operation !!!
 109:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *                  |
 110:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *      -------------------------
 111:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *      | R | W | 2 | 3 | 4 | 5 |
 112:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *
 113:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *      perform write(2), result is still a full fifo.
 114:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *
 115:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *                  |
 116:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *      -------------------------
 117:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  *      | R | 1 | 2 | W | 4 | 5 |
 118:/home/pi/Developer/tinyusb/src/common/tusb_fifo.h ****  */
